snippet.textDisplay:
Happy Level Up Day, and welcome to your 30s! It's all downhill from here, buddy.

Except, it isn't really. By this point we have our personalities settled, and we generally have formed those friendships that matter and last. Funny thing is, most of us no matter how old we get, we feel like the same person inside as we did in our early 20s, or for some late teens.

I'm 32. I don't feel that age. I mean I got married last year, planning to start a family this year, but I'm still sat here like in my head I'm 21 but with a bit more wisdom and experience. I still laugh at farts because laughter is good.

Make sure you're happy what you're doing, keep having fun! Your laughter and enjoyment is infectious in the best way. Husband and I watch your videos, not all of them but you know when there's something we are interested in we enjoy. My time is spent in constant pain (yay chronic illness and disability) on the sofa or in my bed 95% of the time, husband had to quit work to look after me full time. Being able to be distracted by laughter, entertaining videos, it helps keep my mind off the pain and honestly my husband's smile and laugh are the purest things he is an absolute delight.

Thanks for making us laugh ♡ thanks for the entertainment ♡ happy level up day, welcome to your 30s :)

Oh and younger folks...people in their 30s are not boomers, we are generally the children of boomers. So, y'know, the insult for us is "OK Millennial"
